The paper discusses Estimation-of-distribution algorithms (EDAs), which are a type of metaheuristic used in optimization. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Given the focus on optimization and probabilistic models, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses theoretical results and benchmark functions, cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.SE are also possible sub-categories.
